item.dc:creator: TheRealJFalc
item.description:
Sort of are, sort of not. I’ve got a few things I want to finish before the update, because they’re things that are specifically not centered around other things, such as a piano song and a special project. But part of me also wants to wait.

I don’t think I can wait that long to write any new music though, composing music is how I unwind from classes while I’m studying xD

item.title: [Poll] Are You Waiting For the Update to Make New Tracks?
item.dc:creator: akabillposters
item.description:
I’ve got the opposite ‘problem’. Too many ideas. Too many bits started and not developed or partially developed, because I’m distracted by another new idea that’s come along – and ‘demands’ my creative attention.

I’ll be developing ideas into skeletal tracks ahead of the update, but not producing finished pieces (unless the available sounds actually suit the piece).

(Still, I consider anything I produce with Auxy to be demo quality only, so I’m really only aiming for ‘Auxy finished’ as far as the app goes, not [proper] ‘release-ready’.)
